review_blob: From the tap at the brewery. A good stout with some coffee flavors along with malt. Not very strong with any of the flavors but very drinkable. very small off white head with no carbination. A very clean non-bitter finish that instantly make you want to have another one.

At the brewery on tap. Pencil thin white head. Golden brown color with very little carbination. Floral taste with a clean dry finish. A very simple beer with no complexity. Very refreshing that will be great for day drinking.
